args:
While pursuing reports of people being unable
to awaken from slumber, the party is pulled into
a world of dreams. It's a world created by
Peony, a dreamland creature called an ljósálfar
who is corrupted by black mana. In order to
escape, the party must challenge her head-on.
The village I heard about is\njust down the road here.
Here's hopin' we didn't come all this way\njust 'cause a buncha folks are lazy...

Heck, can you blame 'em? All I want to
do on a beautiful day like this is hop
in the sack and catch me some...
*YAAAAAAAAWN*
Do not lower your guard, Luca!\nWe've no idea what awaits us in...\n*YAAAAAAAAAWN*
Even Elisanne is yawning now?\nSomething is very amiss.
I-I'm so sorry! I was just suddenly\noverwhelmed with exhaustion...
*YAAAAAAAAAAWN*\nYeah, I think the ol' sandman\nis comin' for me, too...
This is just like what happened before!\nEveryone became sleepy the moment\nwe approached that village.
I did, my brother did, and then...\n*YAAAAAAAAAWN*\nOh no... It's happening again...
I can't...go on...  I'm going to...
Wake UP already! You're going to catch\nyour death if you fall asleep here.
What is wrong with you, weirdo?\nYou're acting like you've seen a ghost.
I'm sorry, I just... I thought you...
I think half your brain is still asleep.\nBetter shake the lead out, though,\n'cause we need to get moving.
Ah, but I think you know where,\nPrince {player_name}.
Alfonse?! Oh, what a relief to see you!\nWe heard you had been captured.
None of that matters now.\nCome, we must make haste.
I don't understand—where\nexactly are we all GOING?
Look, this is the realm of happy dreams,\nwhich means it's a place for children.\nNow it's time for you to grow up a bit.
Alas, ours is but a world of weapons\nand bloodshed, destruction and war.\nThat is where we belong now.
I'm taking you there now, old friend...\nto our new world of endless nightmares!
Alfonse, stop! What's gotten into you?!
*pant* *pant* Okay, I think\nthis should be far enough...
Sharena, are you... Um...\nWell, is this real?
I was with Prince Alfonse and my sister,\nbut they didn't seem like themselves.\nSo I wondered if you two were...real.
Okay, you are NOT doubting me right now!
Ha ha ha! Hey, it's okay. I get it.\nAnd I promise that I'm your Sharena.
M-my Sharena? Er, I mean...\nI'm glad to hear that.
I am so pleased to see you\nsafe and well, Your Highness.
Looks like we all had a rough go of it.
You have no idea how relieved I am\nto see all of you here!
Er, but why ARE we here, exactly?\nWeren't we just following up a lead\nabout one of Sharena's friends?
Well, I'm not completely sure, but if I had\nto guess, I'd say that we're actually all\nasleep in the world of dreams.
Oh, come on. Don't tell me you're one of\nthose gloomy adults who have forgotten\nhow to dream!
But how can you be so sure\nthat we're in a dream?
Because this isn't the first time this\nsort of thing has happened to me.
I'm definitely feeling some déjà vu here.\nI've fallen into this kind of magical\nslumber before for certain...
And how did you return to the\nreal world last time?
I was rescued by a ljósálfar—\nor what you would call a faerie.
There sure are! In fact, that dream world\nfaerie ended up becoming a dear friend.
She has the power to show people happy\ndreams, so when we were under attack\nfrom nightmares, she...
Dreams are the people's rest...\nDreams are the people's hopes...
Yes, it was just like that, actually.
Peony! Oh, I'm so glad to see you!
Everyone, this is the faerie from the realm\nof dreams I was just telling you about!
Whoa, this lady is GINORMOUS!\n...I mean, for a faerie. No wonder\nyou thought I was so teeny.
Anyway, everything should be\nall right now that Peony is here.
Hold on, Sharena. Doesn't she seem\na bit...odd to you?
This is the realm of dreams.\nIt is a happy place for children.\nGrown-ups do not belong here.
Adults steal happy dreams from children.\nAdults are the real nightmares.\nNightmares...shoo! Away with you!
Away with you! \nAway with you!\nAway with you!
Is she controlling them somehow?\nOr did she actually CREATE them?
Peony would never do that!\nShe and I are friends!
Yeah, on a normal day, I'm sure she is.\nBut I think I see the problem here...
That's what we call ＂black mana.＂ It has\nthe power to corrupt any living creature,\ntwisting it in both body and soul.
No! We have to save Peony!
If we fight her and force her to burn\nthrough all of the black mana that's\ncoursing through her, it should—

I know exactly how you feel, but I promise
that this will end with her salvation.
Stand back, if you like, and let us
take this burden up ourselves.
N-no! I can't ask all of you to\nfight her without me!
I'll...I'll be okay. I mean, even best friends\nfight sometimes, right?
You have it out, and then you're even\nbetter friends than you were before!\nIt's going to be just like that.
Heh. You sure do manage to find the\nbright side of things. Now let's do this!
